On a similar topic, recently in australia there was a case in court where a woman was mugged and stabbed in the stomach. The woman was 7 and a half months pregnent and the baby was killed by the stab. It was proven in court by experts that had the baby been born at 7.5 months it would have survived. However the mugger was not able to be charged with murder because legally the baby was not classified as human at this stage. BTW this has no relation to the above arguements, I think the mugger *SHOULD* have been charged with murder and burn in hell, just thought it might be of interest. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kellianne>Kellianne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/11/02 6:17:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=239.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bestanimations.com/Fantasy/Dragons/Dragon-03.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>HOWEVER, at some stage during the pregnency it does become a human being, no one can deny this. (unless you want us to believe that when a sperm meets and egg it magically becomes human 2 seconds into cell division). Scientifically it has been decided that the fetus becomes a baby human at around the 4th month into pregnency.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
